Thomas F.  Frist III


HCA Healthcare/Investors/Thomas F.  Frist III 













Investors











Login








      Category:          

Board of Directors 



EmailPDFPrintRSS 






 






Thomas Frist III is a principal of Frist Capital, L.L.C., a Nashville-based investment company founded in 1994. Mr. Frist is also a general partner at Frisco Partners, a family investment vehicle. Previously, Mr. Frist co-managed FS Partners, L.L.C. in New York and worked in principal investments at Rainwater, Inc. in Fort Worth, TX and in New York. Mr. Frist also serves as a director of SAIC, Inc. A native of Nashville, he received a B.A. degree from Princeton University and an M.B.A. from Harvard Business School.Tommy enjoys tennis, skiing, golf and aviation. He and his wife, Julie, graduated together from Harvard Business School in 1997. They married soon after. They have three young children at home.  











